<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n13081c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n13" href="#n13081c">N13 (VI.D.3)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n13all.htm#n13081c"> 81(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> yew, apple / cut down / hornbook</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"> Now at the end of seven years, poets and prophets and visioners cut down <mark>the yew</mark> which was over the grave of Baile, and they made a poet&apos;s tablet of it, and they wrote the visions and the espousals and the loves and the courtships of Ulster in it. The <mark>apple</mark> tree which grew over the grave of Aillinn was also <mark>cut down</mark> and in like manner the <mark>courtships of Leinster were written in it</mark>. <small> Douglas Hyde, <a name="SEGL" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#SEGL"><cite title="source">The Story of Early Gaelic Literature</cite></a> (1920) 9</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c05020c" href="c5all.htm#c05020c">VI.C.05:020(c)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
